title: "←[1;31mOSError←[0m: Tracklets are empty. " after uploading the pickle file, video and config file under the Refine Tracklets Tab
body:
OS: Windows 10
DeepLabCut Version: '2.2b8'
Anaconda env used: conda 4.8.5

I have a short video of 12 seconds in which I want to track a few markers. I was able to get upto the point of refine tracklets. When I uploaded the video file, config file and the trackelt data(assuming it is the Demo1DLC_resnet50_Test4Nov18shuffle1_200_bx.pickle file), I got the error shown below- "Tracklets are empty". The Gui was also not launched. Since the video tutorial said that refining tracklets are not necessary for single animal objects, I proceeded to try with the Create Videos tab and entered all the parameters as shown in the tutorial. But then got the second error - 
No filtered data file found in C:\Users\mahat\DeepLabCut-master\DeepLabCut-master\Test4-Mahathy-2020-11-18\videos for video Demo1 and scorer DLC_resnet50_Test4Nov18shuffle1_200 and box tracker. 
 Call "deeplabcut.refine_training_dataset.convert_raw_tracks_to_h5()" prior to plotting the trajectories.
Plots could not be created! Videos were not evaluated with the current scorer DLC_resnet50_Test4Nov18shuffle1_200.

I have also not been able to see trackers on the video labelled "Demo1DLC_resnet50_Test4Nov18shuffle1_200_full"
